1
00:00:01,081 --> 00:00:03,161
DOCTOR: Black hole,
400-mile spaceship.

2
00:00:03,241 --> 00:00:05,361
Time is moving faster

3
00:00:05,441 --> 00:00:08,121
at this end of the ship than the other.

4
00:00:08,201 --> 00:00:10,281
How much longer, Doctor?

5
00:00:10,921 --> 00:00:13,601
RAZOR: To survive, they are
what we must all become.

6
00:00:13,921 --> 00:00:15,321
Please tell me you didn't.

7
00:00:16,041 --> 00:00:18,921
RAZOR: I have been
so looking forward to meeting you.

8
00:00:19,001 --> 00:00:22,481
I waited for you.

9
00:00:34,641 --> 00:00:36,681
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

10
00:01:04,161 --> 00:01:06,161
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

11
00:01:09,081 --> 00:01:11,081
(RUMBLING)

12
00:01:12,401 --> 00:01:14,401
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

13
00:01:15,761 --> 00:01:18,161
-(BELL RINGING)
-(CHILDREN EXCLAIMING)

14
00:01:18,241 --> 00:01:20,281
Everyone under their beds! Now!

15
00:01:20,361 --> 00:01:22,681
-Again?
-Alit, get under your bed

16
00:01:22,761 --> 00:01:24,841
-and stay there.
-(BELL CONTINUES RINGING)

17
00:01:37,441 --> 00:01:38,921
(GUNSHOTS)

18
00:01:41,241 --> 00:01:44,161
-It's the scarecrows. New ones.
-It's okay.

19
00:01:44,241 --> 00:01:46,081
-We'll be okay.
-(GUNFIRE CONTINUES)

20
00:01:46,161 --> 00:01:47,841
MAN: Save your ammo.

21
00:01:47,921 --> 00:01:50,001
Wait for it. Fire!

22
00:02:02,041 --> 00:02:04,401
(RUMBLING)

23
00:02:19,121 --> 00:02:20,481
(GROUND CRACKING)

24
00:02:24,681 --> 00:02:26,681
(RUMBLING)

25
00:02:40,441 --> 00:02:42,041
(CRASHING)

26
00:02:49,001 --> 00:02:51,001
(METAL CLANKING)

27
00:03:01,721 --> 00:03:03,721
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

28
00:03:39,121 --> 00:03:40,721
THE MASTER: How many times
have you died?

29
00:03:40,801 --> 00:03:42,161
(DOCTOR GASPS)

30
00:03:42,241 --> 00:03:44,081
MISSY: How many different ways?

31
00:03:44,161 --> 00:03:45,361
THE MASTER: Have you burned?

32
00:03:46,761 --> 00:03:48,081
I know you've fallen.

33
00:03:49,681 --> 00:03:50,801
(SIGHS)

34
00:03:50,881 --> 00:03:53,361
Have you ever drowned?

35
00:03:55,641 --> 00:03:57,601
-(GASPING)
-Have you felt the blade?

36
00:03:57,681 --> 00:04:01,681
I suppose what we're really asking,
my dear,

37
00:04:01,761 --> 00:04:03,921
is, well...

38
00:04:08,001 --> 00:04:09,521
Any requests?

39
00:04:12,081 --> 00:04:13,081
(GASPS)

40
00:04:15,601 --> 00:04:17,241
(GRUNTS)

41
00:04:17,321 --> 00:04:18,561
(GROANS)

42
00:04:22,441 --> 00:04:23,721
(GASPS)

43
00:04:28,001 --> 00:04:29,601
(THE MASTER LAUGHING MENACINGLY)

44
00:04:36,641 --> 00:04:38,241
(SLOW WALTZ PLAYING)

45
00:04:50,841 --> 00:04:53,481
THE MASTER: So, I imagine
you're the next one along then?

46
00:04:53,561 --> 00:04:56,041
(CLICKS TONGUE) Oh, I think so.

47
00:04:56,121 --> 00:04:59,961
I'm a bit hazy on the whole
regeneration thing, I'm afraid.

48
00:05:00,041 --> 00:05:01,881
You mean,
I'm going to turn into a woman,

49
00:05:01,961 --> 00:05:03,521
and you don't even remember it
happening?

50
00:05:03,601 --> 00:05:07,561
-Oh! (CHUCKLES) Am I a woman now?
-Well, kind of, yeah.

51
00:05:08,521 --> 00:05:10,361
-Hold me.
-Kiss me.

52
00:05:10,441 --> 00:05:12,761
-Make me.
-Do you two want to be alone?

53
00:05:13,641 --> 00:05:15,881
Which, in your case,
would mean more than it usually does.

54
00:05:16,681 --> 00:05:18,721
Ugh! Grandad's back.

55
00:05:18,801 --> 00:05:23,521
We've been debating the best way
to kill you.

56
00:05:23,601 --> 00:05:25,041
Where's Bill?

57
00:05:25,121 --> 00:05:26,801
Well, we thought we might chuck you
off the roof

58
00:05:26,881 --> 00:05:30,441
but I wasn't sure
how many regenerations you had left.

59
00:05:30,521 --> 00:05:32,881
Yeah, we could have been up
and down the stairs all night.

60
00:05:32,961 --> 00:05:34,641
Could shoot you,
but that's a bit vanilla.

61
00:05:34,721 --> 00:05:37,801
-Bit old school. Nice for a change.
-For a change.

62
00:05:37,881 --> 00:05:39,561
I said, where is Bill?

63
00:05:39,641 --> 00:05:41,721
Well, if we told you that,

64
00:05:41,801 --> 00:05:45,801
I'm afraid you'd be really,
really upset.

65
00:05:45,881 --> 00:05:47,801
So...

66
00:05:47,881 --> 00:05:51,041
BOTH: She's right behind you.

67
00:05:52,361 --> 00:05:53,801
MISSY: Look, there's Bill!

68
00:05:53,881 --> 00:05:57,121
Dead, dismembered,
fed through a grinder

69
00:05:57,201 --> 00:05:58,681
and squeezed into a Cyberman,

70
00:05:58,761 --> 00:06:01,641
doomed to spend, er,
an eternal afterlife

71
00:06:01,721 --> 00:06:03,561
as a bio mechanical psycho-zombie.

72
00:06:03,641 --> 00:06:05,561
It was hilarious.

73
00:06:06,361 --> 00:06:11,281
Ten years you spent up there, chatting.
You missed her by two hours.

74
00:06:11,361 --> 00:06:12,601
MISSY: Ripped out her heart,

75
00:06:12,681 --> 00:06:15,561
threw it into a bin
and burned it all away.

76
00:06:16,601 --> 00:06:18,561
He's internalising.

77
00:06:18,641 --> 00:06:20,961
I love it when he's Mr Volcano.

78
00:06:21,041 --> 00:06:25,241
DOCTOR: The last time I saw you,
you were on your way to Gallifrey.

79
00:06:25,321 --> 00:06:28,841
Well, I didn't stay. Why would I stay?

80
00:06:28,921 --> 00:06:31,281
So, they cured your little condition
and kicked you out.

81
00:06:31,361 --> 00:06:33,801
It was a mutual "kicking me out.”

82
00:06:34,921 --> 00:06:38,841
Somehow, you ended up in this dump.
You never could drive.

83
00:06:38,921 --> 00:06:42,081
-Nah, you wouldn't understand.
-DOCTOR: Well, let's see how I do.

84
00:06:42,161 --> 00:06:44,081
Your TARDIS got stuck,

85
00:06:44,161 --> 00:06:46,761
you killed a lot of people,
took over the city,

86
00:06:46,841 --> 00:06:50,601
lived like a king
till they rebelled against your cruelty.

87
00:06:50,681 --> 00:06:53,081
And ever since then,
you've been hiding out,

88
00:06:53,161 --> 00:06:54,401
probably in disguise

89
00:06:54,481 --> 00:06:56,961
because everyone knows
your stupid round face.

90
00:06:59,081 --> 00:07:00,841
-Round?
-It's a little bit...

91
00:07:00,921 --> 00:07:02,001
Shut up!

92
00:07:02,881 --> 00:07:05,241
You want to see my city, Doctor?

93
00:07:05,321 --> 00:07:06,561
Do you want to see what happens

94
00:07:06,641 --> 00:07:09,121
when you're too late
to save your little friend,

95
00:07:09,201 --> 00:07:11,841
and everybody else? See!

96
00:07:12,241 --> 00:07:14,321
This used to be just a hospital.

97
00:07:14,401 --> 00:07:17,481
Now it's mass production.
The Cyber Foundries!

98
00:07:17,561 --> 00:07:22,361
The whole city is a machine
to turn people into Cybermen.

99
00:07:22,441 --> 00:07:27,321
What do you think? Exciting isn't it,
watching the Cybermen getting started?

100
00:07:27,401 --> 00:07:31,281
They always get started.
They happen everywhere there's people.

101
00:07:31,361 --> 00:07:34,281
Mondas, Telos, Earth...

102
00:07:34,361 --> 00:07:36,281
Planet 14, Marinus.

103
00:07:36,601 --> 00:07:38,921
Like sewage, and smart phones,

104
00:07:39,001 --> 00:07:41,801
and Donald Trump,
some things are just inevitable.

105
00:07:41,881 --> 00:07:44,881
MISSY: Doctor?
Doctor, have you done something?

106
00:07:44,961 --> 00:07:45,961
What's happening?

107
00:07:46,041 --> 00:07:49,521
People get the Cybermen wrong.
There is no evil plan, no evil genius,

108
00:07:49,601 --> 00:07:51,561
just parallel evolution.

109
00:07:52,801 --> 00:07:55,121
THE MASTER: Doctor, what have you done?

110
00:07:55,201 --> 00:07:58,081
People plus technology minus humanity.

111
00:07:58,161 --> 00:08:00,641
The internet, cyberspace, Cybermen...

112
00:08:00,721 --> 00:08:04,081
Always read the comments
because one day there'll be an army.

113
00:08:06,121 --> 00:08:07,361
MISSY: Look! They're coming.

114
00:08:09,641 --> 00:08:11,321
They're coming for us.

115
00:08:11,401 --> 00:08:12,961
This doesn't make any sense!

116
00:08:13,041 --> 00:08:14,041
Doesn't it?

117
00:08:14,121 --> 00:08:15,881
THE MASTER:
These Cybermen are primitive,

118
00:08:15,961 --> 00:08:18,201
they're programmed to...
to track human beings

119
00:08:18,281 --> 00:08:19,361
and convert them.

120
00:08:19,441 --> 00:08:21,721
They home in
on human life signs only.

121
00:08:21,801 --> 00:08:23,521
You two, you should know by now,

122
00:08:23,601 --> 00:08:25,001
when you're winning
and I'm in the room,

123
00:08:25,081 --> 00:08:26,401
you're missing something.

124
00:08:26,481 --> 00:08:27,961
What have we missed?

125
00:08:28,481 --> 00:08:30,721
You shouldn't have hit me, Missy.

126
00:08:31,641 --> 00:08:32,841
(GRUNTS)

127
00:08:32,921 --> 00:08:34,841
I was waiting for my chance.

128
00:08:36,881 --> 00:08:40,321
Computer, containing the algorithm
defining human life signs...

129
00:08:40,401 --> 00:08:43,601
I had only time to change one detail,
a single number.

130
00:08:43,681 --> 00:08:45,401
One to a two.

131
00:08:45,481 --> 00:08:47,361
One hearts to two hearts.

132
00:08:49,881 --> 00:08:53,521
-(GASPS)
-I expanded the definition of humanity.

133
00:08:54,561 --> 00:08:58,201
Took 'em a while to update the net
but here we go,

134
00:08:58,281 --> 00:08:59,841
welcome to the menu.

135
00:08:59,921 --> 00:09:02,041
(METAL CLANKING)

136
00:09:05,561 --> 00:09:06,761
(GASPS)

137
00:09:09,881 --> 00:09:11,001
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER BEEPS)

138
00:09:11,081 --> 00:09:12,961
DOCTOR: Now they think
that we count as humans,

139
00:09:13,041 --> 00:09:14,681
and they're going
to fix that in a hurry.

140
00:09:22,121 --> 00:09:24,241
There must be other ways up here.
We can't cover them all.

141
00:09:24,321 --> 00:09:27,881
You can't fight a whole city.
You know the stories.

142
00:09:27,961 --> 00:09:31,041
There's only ever been one way
to stop that many Cybermen.

143
00:09:32,761 --> 00:09:33,761
Me!

144
00:09:38,401 --> 00:09:40,641
Then do it. Stop them.

145
00:09:40,721 --> 00:09:42,961
Begging for your life already.
That's a new record.

146
00:09:43,041 --> 00:09:45,481
I'm not begging you.
I'd rather die than beg you.

147
00:09:45,561 --> 00:09:46,721
Luck day, then.

148
00:09:46,801 --> 00:09:49,401
I can do this. They're not difficult.
They're Cybermen.

149
00:09:49,481 --> 00:09:51,001
Knock yourself out.

150
00:09:53,481 --> 00:09:54,881
Your wish is my command.

151
00:09:56,121 --> 00:09:58,721
I was secretly on your side all along,
you silly sausage.

152
00:09:58,801 --> 00:09:59,841
Is that true?

153
00:09:59,921 --> 00:10:01,481
(SCOFFS) Don't spoil the moment.

154
00:10:03,401 --> 00:10:05,681
Seriously, I need to know, is that true?

155
00:10:07,361 --> 00:10:08,681
It's hard to say. I...

156
00:10:10,681 --> 00:10:11,841
I'm in two minds.

157
00:10:11,921 --> 00:10:14,241
Fortunately,
the other one's unconscious.

158
00:10:23,281 --> 00:10:24,561
Nardole, have you been useful?

159
00:10:24,641 --> 00:10:27,481
NARDOLE: Yeah,
found this in the loading bay.

160
00:10:37,361 --> 00:10:38,761
Shuttle craft.

161
00:10:45,201 --> 00:10:46,801
Get junior up there.

162
00:10:46,881 --> 00:10:47,881
(BOTH GRUNT)

163
00:10:49,201 --> 00:10:51,001
THE MASTER:
(GROANS) You hit me really hard.

164
00:10:51,081 --> 00:10:54,281
Oh, you're telling me? I think...
I think I've still got the bump.

165
00:10:55,721 --> 00:10:57,881
Right. First things first...

166
00:10:57,961 --> 00:10:59,761
(SCREAMING)

167
00:11:00,921 --> 00:11:02,041
(GROANING)

168
00:11:07,401 --> 00:11:09,401
(CYBERMAN SCREAMS)

169
00:11:21,121 --> 00:11:22,441
(WHISPERS) Bill.

170
00:11:24,321 --> 00:11:26,281
-(METAL CLANKS)
-(GASPS)

171
00:11:26,361 --> 00:11:29,081
What was that, Doctor?
You'll only slow us down?

172
00:11:29,161 --> 00:11:31,281
Yeah, I think you're right.

173
00:11:38,201 --> 00:11:40,241
(BEEPING)

174
00:11:43,961 --> 00:11:47,161
The Doctor's dead. He told me
he'd always hated you.

175
00:11:47,241 --> 00:11:48,761
-Let's go.
-No.

176
00:11:48,841 --> 00:11:51,801
Doctor's dead. Told me
he'd always hated you.

177
00:11:51,881 --> 00:11:53,121
Yeah, heard you the first time.

178
00:11:53,201 --> 00:11:55,361
-Tedious.
-NARDOLE: Oi!

179
00:11:55,441 --> 00:11:56,441
Look, we need to get away from here

180
00:11:56,521 --> 00:11:58,001
and find a hole in the roof or make one.

181
00:11:58,081 --> 00:12:00,281
Is there a great, big gun on the front?
That would be good.

182
00:12:00,361 --> 00:12:03,881
-(THUDDING)
-I don't think we're going anywhere.

183
00:12:03,961 --> 00:12:06,041
-(RAPID BEEPING)
-Bill's back.

184
00:12:11,801 --> 00:12:12,921
(GASPS)

185
00:12:18,521 --> 00:12:19,521
Bill?

186
00:12:20,801 --> 00:12:22,361
I will fix this.

187
00:12:23,081 --> 00:12:24,841
I will get you back again,

188
00:12:24,921 --> 00:12:26,201
I swear.

189
00:12:32,681 --> 00:12:35,321
MISSY: What level are we on?
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

190
00:12:35,401 --> 00:12:38,601
THE MASTER: Must be one
of the solar farms.

191
00:12:38,681 --> 00:12:41,321
Hologram sky, a bit of atmosphere.

192
00:12:41,401 --> 00:12:42,721
Who are you?

193
00:12:42,801 --> 00:12:44,641
That's the last floor
we can bust through.

194
00:12:44,721 --> 00:12:46,441
The engine's blown.

195
00:12:46,521 --> 00:12:47,961
Hello, little girl.

196
00:12:48,041 --> 00:12:49,401
We're from downstairs

197
00:12:49,481 --> 00:12:51,801
and, er, I think we're going
to need your help.

198
00:13:20,361 --> 00:13:21,401
(DOOR OPENS)

199
00:13:23,081 --> 00:13:24,081
(DOOR CREAKS)

200
00:13:25,441 --> 00:13:26,561
(DOOR CLOSES)

201
00:13:42,361 --> 00:13:44,241
Sorry you have to stay out here.

202
00:13:45,001 --> 00:13:47,481
You'd frighten the children.

203
00:13:48,481 --> 00:13:49,601
Where am I?

204
00:13:51,001 --> 00:13:52,161
How did I...

205
00:13:52,881 --> 00:13:54,041
Sorry.

206
00:13:54,321 --> 00:13:57,081
-I can't remember...
-HAZRAN: The Doctor put you to sleep.

207
00:13:57,161 --> 00:13:59,161
-You needed rest.
-What am I doing in a barn?

208
00:14:00,801 --> 00:14:02,041
What's wrong?

209
00:14:02,121 --> 00:14:04,201
Sorry. It's just...

210
00:14:06,601 --> 00:14:08,481
-Sorry, what?
-The Doctor has explained

211
00:14:08,561 --> 00:14:10,401
that you're not dangerous, but...

212
00:14:11,361 --> 00:14:12,441
It's difficult.

213
00:14:13,401 --> 00:14:14,721
What's difficult?

214
00:14:15,681 --> 00:14:17,841
(STUTTERS) Where is the Doctor?
I need to sp...

215
00:14:17,921 --> 00:14:19,881
His injuries are, are,
are being tended to...

216
00:14:19,961 --> 00:14:21,281
Injuries?

217
00:14:21,961 --> 00:14:23,921
What... I want to see the Doctor.

218
00:14:24,001 --> 00:14:25,121
-(DOOR OPENS)
-I need to speak to him.

219
00:14:26,161 --> 00:14:27,961
(LOCKING DOOR)

220
00:14:35,841 --> 00:14:37,921
-(DOOR OPENS)
-Hello?

221
00:14:41,161 --> 00:14:42,801
ALIT: Hello.

222
00:14:44,121 --> 00:14:45,921
Everyone's too scared to talk to you

223
00:14:46,921 --> 00:14:48,241
but I'm not.

224
00:14:49,001 --> 00:14:50,921
Why are they scared?

225
00:14:51,001 --> 00:14:53,241
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

226
00:14:53,321 --> 00:14:55,641
NARDOLE: Come on, you lot.
Put your backs into it.

227
00:14:55,721 --> 00:14:57,361
Remember the Alamo.

228
00:14:57,441 --> 00:14:58,481
-(GRUNTS)
-Er, maybe not.

229
00:14:58,561 --> 00:15:03,001
-Nardole, you're working them too hard.
-This isn't work. It's war.

230
00:15:04,161 --> 00:15:06,761
Operation Exodus. They're looking
for fresh meat and you're it.

231
00:15:07,441 --> 00:15:08,561
(DOOR OPENS)

232
00:15:12,601 --> 00:15:13,601
Is that it?

233
00:15:19,041 --> 00:15:21,361
I really wouldn't harm you, you know.

234
00:15:22,121 --> 00:15:23,321
I know.

235
00:15:46,401 --> 00:15:47,601
(GASPS)

236
00:15:58,761 --> 00:16:02,201
BILL: 7hat ls not me.

237
00:16:03,641 --> 00:16:04,881
I'm sorry.

238
00:16:04,961 --> 00:16:08,121
-I am Bill Potts.
-I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

239
00:16:08,201 --> 00:16:11,281
-I am Bill Potts.
-Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

240
00:16:12,881 --> 00:16:15,601
-Hello, Bill Potts.
-BILL: Doctor.

241
00:16:15,681 --> 00:16:18,041
ALIT: I'm sorry. I gave her a mirror.

242
00:16:18,521 --> 00:16:21,761
Oh, no, don't be sorry.
You were being kind.

243
00:16:22,601 --> 00:16:24,401
Nothing wrong with kind. Jelly baby?

244
00:16:25,521 --> 00:16:27,161
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

245
00:16:28,481 --> 00:16:30,561
-Bye.
-Toodle-o0o0.

246
00:16:33,001 --> 00:16:35,321
-(DOOR CLOSES)
-(BILL SIGHS)

247
00:16:47,721 --> 00:16:50,961
-What was that? In the mirror?
-Er... (SNIFFLES)

248
00:16:54,121 --> 00:16:55,121
A Cyberman.

249
00:16:55,801 --> 00:16:57,481
What's a Cyberman?

250
00:16:57,561 --> 00:17:00,241
A technologically-augmented human being

251
00:17:01,241 --> 00:17:03,041
designed to survive
in a hostile environment.

252
00:17:03,121 --> 00:17:04,361
Perfectly sound idea.

253
00:17:04,441 --> 00:17:05,561
Unfortunately,

254
00:17:05,641 --> 00:17:08,921
all they want to do is to turn
everyone else into Cybermen, too.

255
00:17:09,561 --> 00:17:10,961
They go viral.

256
00:17:11,681 --> 00:17:12,801
Why?

257
00:17:14,521 --> 00:17:16,761
They consider themselves
to be an improvement,

258
00:17:16,841 --> 00:17:18,201
-an upgrade.
-No.

259
00:17:19,281 --> 00:17:22,241
Why do I see a Cyberman in the mirror?

260
00:17:40,401 --> 00:17:43,481
-What do you remember?
-Quite a lot, you know?

261
00:17:44,521 --> 00:17:46,281
I was down there for 10 years...

262
00:17:46,641 --> 00:17:50,801
And then, one day,
they took you to the conversion theatre.

263
00:17:50,881 --> 00:17:52,601
-Do you remember that?
-No.

264
00:17:55,321 --> 00:17:58,401
Well, bits of it. I... You turned up.

265
00:18:00,361 --> 00:18:02,161
Do you remember what they did to you?

266
00:18:03,761 --> 00:18:05,001
Nothing.

267
00:18:06,481 --> 00:18:07,921
Look at me, I'm fine.

268
00:18:11,721 --> 00:18:13,041
I'm fine!

269
00:18:28,881 --> 00:18:31,601
You are so strong,

270
00:18:33,081 --> 00:18:34,321
amazing.

271
00:18:35,441 --> 00:18:39,561
Your mind has rebelled against
the programming.

272
00:18:39,641 --> 00:18:42,641
It's built a wall around itself,
a castle made of you

273
00:18:42,721 --> 00:18:46,281
and you are standing on the battlements
saying, "No. No, not me."

274
00:18:46,361 --> 00:18:48,281
What are you talking about?

275
00:18:48,361 --> 00:18:51,401
DOCTOR: All that time,
living under the Monks,

276
00:18:51,481 --> 00:18:53,081
you learned to hang on to yourself.

277
00:18:53,641 --> 00:18:54,841
(GASPS)

278
00:18:54,921 --> 00:18:57,801
But, I'm... I'm fine! Look at me!

279
00:19:00,841 --> 00:19:02,041
Bill...

280
00:19:04,081 --> 00:19:05,241
What you see is not you.

281
00:19:06,961 --> 00:19:09,121
Your mind is acting like
a perception filter.

282
00:19:09,201 --> 00:19:13,361
You still see yourself
as you used to be.

283
00:19:13,441 --> 00:19:14,841
Used to be?

284
00:19:14,921 --> 00:19:16,961
-It won't last...
-What do you mean

285
00:19:17,041 --> 00:19:18,401
"used to be"?

286
00:19:23,801 --> 00:19:26,521
Bill, I'm sorry but you can't
be angry any more.

287
00:19:26,601 --> 00:19:28,441
A temper is a luxury you cannot...

288
00:19:28,521 --> 00:19:29,521
Why can't I?

289
00:19:30,761 --> 00:19:32,441
Why can't I be angry?

290
00:19:32,521 --> 00:19:34,161
Bill, please.

291
00:19:34,241 --> 00:19:36,081
BILL: You left me alone for 10...

292
00:19:36,161 --> 00:19:38,561
...years!
Don't tell me, I can't be angry!

293
00:19:40,881 --> 00:19:42,721
(ALL SCREAMING)

294
00:19:43,681 --> 00:19:44,681
MAN: Move back.

295
00:19:45,521 --> 00:19:46,681
-You, all right?
-(GASPS)

296
00:19:46,761 --> 00:19:48,601
-Because of that.
-MAN: Stand there.

297
00:19:49,521 --> 00:19:51,281
DOCTOR: That's why.

298
00:19:51,361 --> 00:19:54,441
-(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)
-Because you're a Cyberman.

299
00:19:56,961 --> 00:20:00,001
Right. Everyone back to work.

300
00:20:00,081 --> 00:20:04,201
Nothing to see here.
Somebody broke the barn. No biggie.

301
00:20:06,481 --> 00:20:08,801
Come on,
defences don't build themselves.

302
00:20:08,881 --> 00:20:11,961
DOCTOR: It's okay.
They're just frightened.

303
00:20:13,041 --> 00:20:16,561
(SOBS) People are always going
to be afraid of me, aren't they?

304
00:20:18,161 --> 00:20:19,601
Aren't they?

305
00:20:35,201 --> 00:20:36,721
What is that? Engine oil?

306
00:20:36,801 --> 00:20:38,201
No. It's an actual tear.

307
00:20:39,561 --> 00:20:41,281
It shouldn't be.

308
00:20:41,361 --> 00:20:42,561
Doctor.

309
00:20:43,961 --> 00:20:46,921
Right. While you've been here
chatting up Robo-mop,

310
00:20:47,001 --> 00:20:49,761
me and me have been busy.

311
00:20:49,841 --> 00:20:51,201
We found it.

312
00:20:52,321 --> 00:20:54,121
(AS RAZOR) Oh, hello, my dear.

313
00:20:55,201 --> 00:20:58,961
My God, you were so boring
for all those years.

314
00:20:59,041 --> 00:21:00,841
(THE MASTER LAUGHING)

315
00:21:00,921 --> 00:21:04,921
But it was worth every day of it

316
00:21:05,721 --> 00:21:08,161
-for this.
-Bill, don't let him upset you.

317
00:21:09,041 --> 00:21:10,641
Though, didn't you used to be a woman?

318
00:21:10,721 --> 00:21:13,121
I'm going to be a woman. Fairly soon.
Any tips?

319
00:21:14,361 --> 00:21:18,001
Or maybe, I don't know, old bras?

320
00:21:18,081 --> 00:21:20,601
I am not upset.

321
00:21:20,681 --> 00:21:24,161
Oh. Well, doesn't that
take all the fun out of cruelty?

322
00:21:24,241 --> 00:21:26,921
Might as well rile a fridge.
Come on, this way.

323
00:21:39,001 --> 00:21:41,241
Why are there so many children
in the house?

324
00:21:41,321 --> 00:21:43,921
Small community.
Several hundred at most,

325
00:21:44,001 --> 00:21:47,681
so they keep the children together
for their protection.

326
00:21:48,641 --> 00:21:51,241
Those things,
they make it up here sometimes.

327
00:21:51,321 --> 00:21:54,361
They try to take the children...
(GROANING)

328
00:21:55,801 --> 00:21:56,881
Are you all right?

329
00:21:58,481 --> 00:21:59,681
Yes, fine.

330
00:21:59,761 --> 00:22:01,041
(SIGHS)

331
00:22:02,281 --> 00:22:03,281
What was that?

332
00:22:03,641 --> 00:22:05,561
Er, they target the children

333
00:22:05,641 --> 00:22:07,481
because conversion is easy
with a younger donor.

334
00:22:07,561 --> 00:22:09,441
The brains are fresher,

335
00:22:09,521 --> 00:22:13,441
and because their bodies are smaller
there's less to, er... (PANTS)

336
00:22:14,961 --> 00:22:16,081
Less to what?

337
00:22:17,201 --> 00:22:18,961
Less to throw away.

338
00:22:24,121 --> 00:22:28,081
You said... I remember,
you said you could fix this.

339
00:22:29,401 --> 00:22:30,681
That you could get me back.

340
00:22:32,481 --> 00:22:34,481
-Did you say that?
- I did say that. Yes.

341
00:22:34,561 --> 00:22:35,921
-Were you lying?
-No.

342
00:22:38,721 --> 00:22:41,401
-Were you right?
-No.

343
00:22:43,001 --> 00:22:44,281
(SIGHS)

344
00:22:46,641 --> 00:22:47,961
Bill.

345
00:22:48,041 --> 00:22:50,281
We're not going to get out of this one,
are we?

346
00:22:50,361 --> 00:22:51,561
Well...

347
00:22:52,721 --> 00:22:54,481
I don't know.

348
00:22:54,961 --> 00:22:56,961
There are always possibilities.

349
00:22:58,401 --> 00:22:59,841
I can feel it.

350
00:23:01,001 --> 00:23:02,801
In my head, the programming...

351
00:23:04,481 --> 00:23:07,081
The Cybermen are taking me over,
piece by piece.

352
00:23:08,721 --> 00:23:12,881
It's like I'm hanging on in a hurricane,
and I can't hang on forever.

353
00:23:12,961 --> 00:23:15,881
-Bill, look. Whatever it takes...
-No, I want you to know,

354
00:23:15,961 --> 00:23:17,321
as my friend...

355
00:23:20,921 --> 00:23:24,921
I don't want to live
if I can't be me any more.

356
00:23:27,241 --> 00:23:29,921
-Do you understand?
-Yeah.

357
00:23:33,001 --> 00:23:34,441
And that's not possible, is it?

358
00:23:36,841 --> 00:23:38,841
I'll tell you what else isn't possible.

359
00:23:40,081 --> 00:23:42,041
A Cyberman crying.

360
00:23:42,121 --> 00:23:44,921
Where there's tears, there's hope.

361
00:23:46,241 --> 00:23:47,561
Come on.

362
00:23:51,801 --> 00:23:55,281
Weird, how you don't remember
any of this.

363
00:23:55,361 --> 00:23:57,841
Two of us together pushed
the timelines out of sync.

364
00:23:57,921 --> 00:24:00,881
You can't retain your memory,
so I don't have them.

365
00:24:02,921 --> 00:24:05,201
You absolutely had to bring her,
did you?

366
00:24:06,441 --> 00:24:08,721
Her? It's a Cyberman now.

367
00:24:08,801 --> 00:24:10,321
Yeah, sorry.

368
00:24:10,401 --> 00:24:14,441
Becoming a woman is one thing,
but have you got empathy?

369
00:24:15,441 --> 00:24:16,601
DOCTOR: Where is it?

370
00:24:16,681 --> 00:24:18,521
MISSY: Lift shaft, right here.

371
00:24:19,441 --> 00:24:22,001
THE MASTER: Hologram.
Mustn't ruin the pretty forest.

372
00:24:22,081 --> 00:24:24,321
It's a wonder more people
don't turn to genocide.

373
00:24:24,401 --> 00:24:26,001
And the doors...

374
00:24:26,721 --> 00:24:29,481
DOCTOR: This is how we evacuate
the children.

375
00:24:29,561 --> 00:24:31,881
There have to be more lifts.
Quite close.

376
00:24:33,321 --> 00:24:36,721
We know Operation Exodus is ready.
We can't hang around here.

377
00:24:38,321 --> 00:24:40,361
-(BEEPS)
-DOCTOR: What are you doing?

378
00:24:40,441 --> 00:24:41,801
You just called the Lift!

379
00:24:41,881 --> 00:24:43,441
Yeah, but we're going to need them,
aren't we?

380
00:24:43,521 --> 00:24:47,401
The lift was downstairs
and, quite possibly, not empty.

381
00:24:47,481 --> 00:24:48,721
(RAPID BEEPING)

382
00:24:48,801 --> 00:24:50,841
Stand aside.

383
00:24:51,921 --> 00:24:54,161
-Do as she says.
-Stand aside.

384
00:24:54,241 --> 00:24:58,001
"Do as she says."
Is the future going to be all girl?

385
00:24:58,081 --> 00:24:59,321
We can only hope.

386
00:24:59,401 --> 00:25:01,481
(RAPID BEEPING)

387
00:25:01,561 --> 00:25:03,721
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

388
00:25:13,881 --> 00:25:15,441
(RAPID BEEPING)

389
00:25:15,521 --> 00:25:16,961
(LIFT DINGS)

390
00:25:17,041 --> 00:25:18,161
Fire!

391
00:25:18,241 --> 00:25:20,281
THE MASTER: Kill it, kill it,
kill it, kill it, kill it.

392
00:25:20,361 --> 00:25:22,201
(BILL GRUNTING)

393
00:25:22,281 --> 00:25:23,521
Kill it!

394
00:25:27,161 --> 00:25:29,481
Missy, sonic the lift. Keep it here.

395
00:25:30,481 --> 00:25:32,881
Why is it different?
Why does it look like that?

396
00:25:32,961 --> 00:25:35,881
-It evolved.
-Exactly. Since we left,

397
00:25:35,961 --> 00:25:38,601
they built a weapons-grade version
to come after us

398
00:25:38,681 --> 00:25:40,321
and we just gave our position away.

399
00:25:40,401 --> 00:25:41,721
Well done, the genius twins!

400
00:25:41,801 --> 00:25:43,961
It doesn't matter.
We can still get out of here.

401
00:25:44,041 --> 00:25:47,201
We go take the lift to right to the top
and escape in your TARDIS.

402
00:25:47,321 --> 00:25:51,081
We could evacuate the Waltons back there
if you're feeling ridiculous.

403
00:25:51,161 --> 00:25:52,561
We can't go back to the bridge.

404
00:25:52,641 --> 00:25:55,241
We can go only four,
five floors up at the most.

405
00:25:55,321 --> 00:25:57,921
The further we move up the ship,
the slower time moves for us

406
00:25:58,001 --> 00:26:00,241
and the faster it moves
for the Cybermen.

407
00:26:00,321 --> 00:26:01,721
By the time we get to the bridge

408
00:26:01,801 --> 00:26:04,841
they'll have had thousands of years
to work out how to stop us.

409
00:26:04,921 --> 00:26:07,441
There is no safe way
to get back to the TARDIS.

410
00:26:07,521 --> 00:26:09,921
It's a mathematical impossibility.

411
00:26:10,001 --> 00:26:13,601
CYBER CONTROL: Operation Exodus.
Troops to attack phase.

412
00:26:21,641 --> 00:26:24,001
(ALARM BLARING)

413
00:26:26,201 --> 00:26:27,801
Nardole, what is that?

414
00:26:42,321 --> 00:26:44,761
-(LOW RUMBLE)
-Tell me, what is it?

415
00:26:44,841 --> 00:26:47,361
-NARDOLE: Doctor?
-The Cybermen don't have fear,

416
00:26:47,441 --> 00:26:49,041
but they know how to use it.

417
00:26:49,121 --> 00:26:53,201
Operation Exodus.
They're announcing their arrival.

418
00:26:53,281 --> 00:26:54,801
They're coming!

419
00:26:56,361 --> 00:26:57,881
The Cybermen are coming.

420
00:27:04,121 --> 00:27:05,681
BILL: How long till they get here?

421
00:27:05,761 --> 00:27:09,401
200 miles of time-dilated spaceship,
according to my calculations.

422
00:27:09,481 --> 00:27:10,801
We need a plan. Quick.

423
00:27:11,841 --> 00:27:14,241
You realise this is hopeless,
don't you?

424
00:27:14,321 --> 00:27:16,481
Oh, I was hoping someone would say that.

425
00:27:16,561 --> 00:27:19,081
For a moment there,
I was feeling a glimmer of purpose.

426
00:27:21,321 --> 00:27:22,561
BILL: But do we have long enough?

427
00:27:22,881 --> 00:27:26,681
They're Cybermen.
There's no such thing as long enough.

428
00:27:27,521 --> 00:27:30,721
HAZRAN: But Nardole, look at it,
they've got arm our.

429
00:27:30,801 --> 00:27:32,961
We don't have guns
that can shoot through arm our.

430
00:27:33,041 --> 00:27:35,081
Look, give me one of them rifles.

431
00:27:35,161 --> 00:27:37,081
(WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
IN DISTANCE)

432
00:27:43,681 --> 00:27:47,521
Dearest, I've been thinking,
we need your TARDIS.

433
00:27:47,601 --> 00:27:49,521
We can't go up, but we can go down.

434
00:27:49,601 --> 00:27:52,641
Your TARDIS is right at the bottom
of the ship, isn't it?

435
00:27:53,681 --> 00:27:54,881
Well, I suppose.

436
00:27:54,961 --> 00:27:57,001
Is it or isn't it?

437
00:27:57,081 --> 00:27:58,841
(DOCTOR GRUNTS)

438
00:28:02,961 --> 00:28:04,361
BILL: What's that?

439
00:28:04,441 --> 00:28:07,121
We're on a spaceship, remember?

440
00:28:07,201 --> 00:28:08,841
That's a service duct.

441
00:28:10,361 --> 00:28:13,801
Rusted shut.
Think you could get angry with it?

442
00:28:16,441 --> 00:28:18,161
Is that windmill important?

443
00:28:18,641 --> 00:28:19,721
Why?

444
00:28:19,801 --> 00:28:20,921
(GUNSHOT)

445
00:28:21,761 --> 00:28:22,961
-(GASPS)
-(PEOPLE SCREAM)

446
00:28:25,761 --> 00:28:27,161
No reason.

447
00:28:37,561 --> 00:28:40,361
See that bush over there?
Shoot it.

448
00:28:44,241 --> 00:28:46,281
(ALL GASPING)

449
00:28:46,961 --> 00:28:48,761
You think you're quite something,
don't you?

450
00:28:49,321 --> 00:28:50,641
Try not to miss the obvious.

451
00:28:50,721 --> 00:28:52,401
How was that possible?

452
00:28:52,481 --> 00:28:54,241
Because this is not the countryside.

453
00:28:54,321 --> 00:28:56,761
This is a spaceship.

454
00:28:58,281 --> 00:29:01,401
-THE MASTER: It's my TARDIS.
-Our TARDIS.

455
00:29:01,481 --> 00:29:04,681
And it's right in the middle of a city
full of Cybermen.

456
00:29:04,761 --> 00:29:06,001
They are all coming here.

457
00:29:06,081 --> 00:29:08,361
-And it doesn't work!
-Because?

458
00:29:09,401 --> 00:29:12,361
If it fooled you,
it will fool the Cybermen.

459
00:29:12,441 --> 00:29:15,761
They're robots, but they've got
monkey brains.

460
00:29:16,961 --> 00:29:20,601
You can always fool a monkey brain
with a little bit of theatre.

461
00:29:20,681 --> 00:29:25,281
I landed here. I had trouble taking off.

462
00:29:25,361 --> 00:29:28,161
-The black hole?
-Too close to the event horizon.

463
00:29:28,241 --> 00:29:30,921
And you screwed up. You went too fast.

464
00:29:31,001 --> 00:29:33,161
I blew the dematerialisation circuit.

465
00:29:33,241 --> 00:29:36,601
Which reminds me.
A funny thing happened to me once.

466
00:29:36,681 --> 00:29:38,041
What?

467
00:29:39,841 --> 00:29:43,761
A very long time ago, a very scary lady
threw me against a wall

468
00:29:43,841 --> 00:29:49,281
and made me promise to always, always
carry a spare dematerialisation circuit.

469
00:29:50,761 --> 00:29:54,361
I don't remember much about her now

470
00:29:54,441 --> 00:29:57,281
but she must have made
quite an impression.

471
00:29:59,401 --> 00:30:02,801
You know you basically have me
to thank for this.

472
00:30:02,881 --> 00:30:04,401
You're welcome.

473
00:30:05,561 --> 00:30:07,801
By the way, is it wrong that I...

474
00:30:08,801 --> 00:30:09,881
Yes.

475
00:30:10,521 --> 00:30:11,721
-Very.
-(GULPS)

476
00:30:15,561 --> 00:30:19,081
-I don't understand.
-Well, it's very simple, you see.

477
00:30:19,161 --> 00:30:23,161
The Cybermen have removed all fear

478
00:30:23,241 --> 00:30:25,721
from their hearts and from their minds,

479
00:30:25,801 --> 00:30:29,361
but you, Alit,
you're going to put it all back.

480
00:31:13,841 --> 00:31:15,441
HAZRAN: I've never met anyone like you.

481
00:31:16,001 --> 00:31:17,361
So where are you from?

482
00:31:18,681 --> 00:31:21,441
I don't know. I was sort of found.

483
00:31:22,721 --> 00:31:24,161
On a doorstep?

484
00:31:30,561 --> 00:31:32,961
Who loved you?

485
00:31:36,361 --> 00:31:37,361
I, er,

486
00:31:38,441 --> 00:31:39,961
probably should tell you,

487
00:31:40,841 --> 00:31:42,001
I'm not human.

488
00:31:42,841 --> 00:31:44,721
I'll try anything once.

489
00:31:47,041 --> 00:31:48,641
(METAL CLANKING)

490
00:31:51,241 --> 00:31:54,721
No! Stop! Stop, stop!
It's Bill! It's Bill!

491
00:31:56,921 --> 00:31:58,001
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

492
00:31:59,561 --> 00:32:01,361
I'm so sorry.

493
00:32:02,321 --> 00:32:05,081
BILL: 7 understand.

494
00:32:15,321 --> 00:32:16,641
Listen, er...

495
00:32:21,121 --> 00:32:23,521
I don't suppose...

496
00:32:23,601 --> 00:32:24,881
(EXPLOSION)

497
00:32:24,961 --> 00:32:26,721
(RUMBLING)

498
00:32:27,721 --> 00:32:29,721
(FIRING)

499
00:32:34,081 --> 00:32:36,561
We've a maximum of 10 minutes
before they attack.

500
00:32:37,841 --> 00:32:39,161
Is it time?

501
00:32:39,241 --> 00:32:41,161
-Nardole?
-We're ready.

502
00:32:42,761 --> 00:32:44,321
-Is that my gun?
-Oh.

503
00:32:44,401 --> 00:32:46,041
Uh, no, no. I don't like guns.

504
00:32:47,201 --> 00:32:48,681
I've got a better idea.

505
00:32:50,441 --> 00:32:51,681
Are you good at throwing?

506
00:32:51,761 --> 00:32:52,761
Better than all the boys.

507
00:32:52,841 --> 00:32:55,561
Then how about humanity's first weapon?

508
00:32:57,401 --> 00:32:59,361
Tempting, isn't it?

509
00:33:03,801 --> 00:33:09,841
Listen, me and sis are off now
but we were kind of wondering...

510
00:33:09,921 --> 00:33:11,761
What's your plan, Doc?

511
00:33:11,841 --> 00:33:14,601
Because whatever you've got,
you can't save them.

512
00:33:14,681 --> 00:33:17,401
There's another solar farm
five levels above us.

513
00:33:17,481 --> 00:33:19,081
If I can get all the children up there,

514
00:33:19,161 --> 00:33:22,081
-and most of the adults...
-Then the Cybermen will find them again.

515
00:33:23,401 --> 00:33:26,041
It's the best I can do, so I'm doing it.
Do you have a problem with that?

516
00:33:26,521 --> 00:33:27,681
You can't win.

517
00:33:27,761 --> 00:33:29,241
I know. And?

518
00:33:30,801 --> 00:33:33,921
(CHUCKLES) Come on, lady version,

519
00:33:34,321 --> 00:33:36,281
I honestly don't know
what you see in him.

520
00:33:38,241 --> 00:33:39,521
Likewise.

521
00:33:43,121 --> 00:33:44,241
No!

522
00:33:47,841 --> 00:33:48,961
No!

523
00:33:50,361 --> 00:33:53,401
When I say "No,"
you turn back around. Hey!

524
00:33:55,041 --> 00:33:57,201
I'm gonna be dead in a few hours,
so before I go,

525
00:33:57,281 --> 00:33:59,881
let's have this out, you and me,
once and for all.

526
00:34:01,521 --> 00:34:02,561
(SCOFFS)

527
00:34:04,761 --> 00:34:05,961
Winning?

528
00:34:06,041 --> 00:34:07,601
Is that what you think it's about?

529
00:34:08,561 --> 00:34:09,841
I'm not trying to win.

530
00:34:10,281 --> 00:34:13,481
I'm not doing this
because I want to beat someone

531
00:34:13,561 --> 00:34:15,401
or 'cause I hate someone or because...

532
00:34:15,481 --> 00:34:16,921
Because I want to blame someone.

533
00:34:17,601 --> 00:34:18,721
It's not because it's fun.

534
00:34:19,121 --> 00:34:20,961
God knows it's not because it's easy.

535
00:34:21,041 --> 00:34:23,641
It's not even because it works
because it hardly ever does.

536
00:34:23,721 --> 00:34:25,641
I do what I do because it's right!

537
00:34:26,081 --> 00:34:27,321
Because it's decent.

538
00:34:29,161 --> 00:34:31,641
And above all, it's kind.

539
00:34:32,921 --> 00:34:34,081
It's just that.

540
00:34:40,281 --> 00:34:41,641
Just kind.

541
00:34:44,481 --> 00:34:45,801
If I run away today,

542
00:34:47,361 --> 00:34:48,841
good people will die.

543
00:34:49,521 --> 00:34:52,761
If I stand and fight,
some of them might live.

544
00:34:52,841 --> 00:34:54,601
Maybe not many, maybe not for long.

545
00:34:54,681 --> 00:34:57,881
Hey, you know, maybe there's
no point in any of this at all,

546
00:34:57,961 --> 00:34:59,321
but it's the best I can do.

547
00:35:00,721 --> 00:35:03,921
So I'm gonna do it and I will
stand here, doing it, till it kills me.

548
00:35:04,001 --> 00:35:05,841
You're going to die, too...

549
00:35:08,801 --> 00:35:10,361
Someday.

550
00:35:13,401 --> 00:35:14,841
How will that be?
Have you thought about it?

551
00:35:16,001 --> 00:35:17,441
What would you die for?

552
00:35:17,881 --> 00:35:20,601
Who I am, it's where I stand.

553
00:35:20,681 --> 00:35:22,481
Where I stand...

554
00:35:27,721 --> 00:35:29,561
is where I fall.

555
00:35:38,561 --> 00:35:39,841
Stand with me.

556
00:35:40,201 --> 00:35:42,801
These people are terrified.
Maybe we can help.

557
00:35:43,281 --> 00:35:44,401
A little.

558
00:35:44,761 --> 00:35:47,041
Why not, just at the end,

559
00:35:47,921 --> 00:35:49,081
just be kind?

560
00:35:55,161 --> 00:35:56,441
See this face?

561
00:35:57,841 --> 00:36:01,321
Take a good, long look at it.

562
00:36:02,321 --> 00:36:07,241
This is the face that didn't listen
to a word you just said.

563
00:36:20,921 --> 00:36:22,001
Missy?

564
00:36:23,681 --> 00:36:24,761
Missy.

565
00:36:28,841 --> 00:36:31,681
-You've changed. I know you have.
-(SCOFFS)

566
00:36:33,121 --> 00:36:34,721
And I know what you're capable of.

567
00:36:37,161 --> 00:36:38,521
Stand with me.

568
00:36:39,561 --> 00:36:40,921
It's all I've ever wanted.

569
00:36:43,681 --> 00:36:44,921
Me, too.

570
00:36:51,161 --> 00:36:53,241
But no. Sorry.

571
00:36:55,121 --> 00:36:56,281
Just...

572
00:36:57,201 --> 00:36:58,361
No.

573
00:37:01,481 --> 00:37:03,081
But thanks for trying.

574
00:37:24,801 --> 00:37:26,081
Hello.

575
00:37:26,161 --> 00:37:30,521
You will not be harmed.
You will be upgraded.

576
00:37:30,921 --> 00:37:32,241
No, thanks.

577
00:37:37,721 --> 00:37:38,721
(BEEPS)

578
00:37:45,441 --> 00:37:47,161
Alit, let's go.

579
00:38:12,521 --> 00:38:13,681
(SIGHS)

580
00:38:14,001 --> 00:38:16,641
Do you get it now?
This whole floor under the soil,

581
00:38:16,721 --> 00:38:19,041
it's... It's fuel lines
and fusion turbos,

582
00:38:19,121 --> 00:38:22,001
and if you happen to be a genius
with insane computer skills,

583
00:38:22,081 --> 00:38:25,001
you can remote spark
a critical failure and, boom!

584
00:38:26,081 --> 00:38:27,801
You weren't listening
to a word of that, were you?

585
00:38:28,361 --> 00:38:30,281
No, I'm still not getting it.

586
00:38:30,361 --> 00:38:32,521
MAN: Incoming, about 120 feet.

587
00:38:32,601 --> 00:38:36,161
On it. Three, two, one.

588
00:38:39,881 --> 00:38:42,521
So any second now,
the Cybermen will decide

589
00:38:42,601 --> 00:38:46,041
-that we have significant weaponry.
-Awesome weaponry.

590
00:38:46,121 --> 00:38:48,041
NARDOLE: The ultimate apple upgrade.

591
00:38:48,121 --> 00:38:52,201
Which means that they will change
their campaign parameters.

592
00:38:52,281 --> 00:38:53,561
NARDOLE: How's that?

593
00:38:55,801 --> 00:38:58,041
Up till now, this has been
a mercy mission.

594
00:38:58,121 --> 00:38:59,881
-A what?
-DOCTOR: They want to upgrade you.

595
00:39:01,121 --> 00:39:03,121
That's why they come for your children.

596
00:39:03,801 --> 00:39:05,321
But now they think,
we're a military target.

597
00:39:05,401 --> 00:39:08,841
They'll fall back, regroup,
plan a much bigger assault.

598
00:39:08,921 --> 00:39:10,001
Oh. Good-o.

599
00:39:10,081 --> 00:39:11,961
Yes, good

600
00:39:12,041 --> 00:39:13,921
because they will stop tracking
the children, which means...

601
00:39:14,001 --> 00:39:15,361
They're moving back!

602
00:39:17,081 --> 00:39:18,361
Time to go.

603
00:39:18,801 --> 00:39:20,561
But we're surrounded.

604
00:39:20,641 --> 00:39:23,281
Oh, I love being surrounded.
It means everyone's looking at me.

605
00:39:24,241 --> 00:39:27,201
-Okay, Hazran, let's get going.
-Right, then.

606
00:39:27,281 --> 00:39:29,921
HAZRAN: Come on, you lot.
Everyone down to the cellar.

607
00:39:30,001 --> 00:39:32,001
DOCTOR: Nardole, I want you
to lead the evacuation.

608
00:39:32,441 --> 00:39:34,081
What? No.

609
00:39:34,161 --> 00:39:36,841
There's another solar farm on floor 502.

610
00:39:36,921 --> 00:39:38,641
Should be enough livestock
in the cryogenic chamber...

611
00:39:38,721 --> 00:39:40,161
(STAMMERS) You need me with you.

612
00:39:45,281 --> 00:39:48,681
Thanks for all the software.
I will take it from here.

613
00:39:48,761 --> 00:39:51,241
Sir, with respect,
I'm worried about your plan.

614
00:39:51,561 --> 00:39:53,121
Plan? What plan?

615
00:39:53,201 --> 00:39:54,841
I think as soon as this place
is evacuated,

616
00:39:54,921 --> 00:39:57,681
you're gonna blow the whole floor,
killing as many Cybermen as you can.

617
00:39:57,761 --> 00:39:59,321
No. No.

618
00:39:59,401 --> 00:40:01,441
Of course not, I won't do that
until I've left.

619
00:40:01,521 --> 00:40:03,521
Liar! It can't be done remotely.

620
00:40:03,601 --> 00:40:06,001
-You couldn't do it remotely.
-Neither could you.

621
00:40:06,081 --> 00:40:07,801
And more to the point, you're not
sending me up there

622
00:40:07,881 --> 00:40:10,241
to babysit a load of smelly humans.

623
00:40:10,321 --> 00:40:12,881
Yeah, well, I'm afraid that's exactly
what I'm doing.

624
00:40:13,441 --> 00:40:16,401
(CHUCKLES) What?
This is me we're talking about. Me.

625
00:40:17,481 --> 00:40:19,161
You know what I was like.

626
00:40:19,241 --> 00:40:21,801
There's more than three people
in a room, I'll start a black market.

627
00:40:22,321 --> 00:40:24,081
Send me with them,
I'll be selling their own spaceship

628
00:40:24,161 --> 00:40:25,281
back to them once a week.

629
00:40:25,361 --> 00:40:28,841
Please, I would rather
stay down here and explode.

630
00:40:29,401 --> 00:40:31,881
-You go and farm the humans.
-Listen.

631
00:40:32,961 --> 00:40:36,521
One of us has to stay down here
and blow up a lot of silly tin men

632
00:40:36,601 --> 00:40:38,161
and one of us has to go up there

633
00:40:38,241 --> 00:40:42,161
and look after a lot of very
scared people, day after day,

634
00:40:42,241 --> 00:40:44,561
for the rest of their lives,
and keep them safe.

635
00:40:45,481 --> 00:40:47,281
Now the question is this, Nardole.

636
00:40:48,561 --> 00:40:50,081
Which one of us is stronger?

637
00:40:59,721 --> 00:41:00,841
Damn.

638
00:41:09,721 --> 00:41:11,041
(SOFTLY) My condolences.

639
00:41:13,001 --> 00:41:14,681
NARDOLE: I'm gonna
name a town after you.

640
00:41:14,761 --> 00:41:16,361
A really rubbish one.

641
00:41:16,441 --> 00:41:18,521
-Oh, I'm counting on it.
-And probably a pig.

642
00:41:20,401 --> 00:41:23,121
Young lady, you're coming with me,
no arguments.

643
00:41:23,201 --> 00:41:25,921
May I remind you, I'm still empowered
to kick your arse.

644
00:41:26,201 --> 00:41:28,601
You'd have to go back down there
to that hospital and find it, then.

645
00:41:29,361 --> 00:41:31,961
-Look, Bill...
-My arse got kicked a long time ago,

646
00:41:32,201 --> 00:41:33,921
and there's no going back.

647
00:41:39,561 --> 00:41:40,721
All I've got left

648
00:41:41,041 --> 00:41:44,201
-is returning the favour.
-Oh, great, so she"s allowed to explode.

649
00:41:44,281 --> 00:41:45,561
You sure?

650
00:41:47,761 --> 00:41:49,081
(SOFTLY) You know I am.

651
00:41:52,841 --> 00:41:54,481
Well, I don't know what to say.

652
00:41:55,121 --> 00:41:56,921
You'll think of the right words later.

653
00:41:58,601 --> 00:41:59,921
(INHALES SHARPLY)

654
00:42:01,241 --> 00:42:02,361
Doctor.

655
00:42:05,601 --> 00:42:06,601
Bill.

656
00:42:12,641 --> 00:42:14,041
You're wrong, you know.

657
00:42:14,521 --> 00:42:15,681
Quite wrong.

658
00:42:16,521 --> 00:42:18,441
I never will be able to find the words.

659
00:42:23,841 --> 00:42:25,121
(RECEDING FOOTSTEPS)

660
00:42:26,721 --> 00:42:27,881
Right, everyone.

661
00:42:28,001 --> 00:42:30,801
I need you to be big,
I need you to be brave,

662
00:42:30,881 --> 00:42:32,561
and I need you to follow me.

663
00:42:39,281 --> 00:42:40,321
(DEVICE BEEPS)

664
00:42:43,201 --> 00:42:44,201
(LIFT BELL DINGS)

665
00:42:46,881 --> 00:42:50,001
Right. Come on, then. Hop in.
Straight down, TARDIS.

666
00:42:50,481 --> 00:42:51,561
Come here.

667
00:42:53,401 --> 00:42:54,401
THE MASTER: I'm sorry?

668
00:42:57,161 --> 00:42:58,281
Come here, I said.

669
00:42:59,721 --> 00:43:01,281
(CHUCKLES) Seriously?

670
00:43:03,721 --> 00:43:05,041
Are we really gonna do this?

671
00:43:14,361 --> 00:43:15,601
MISSY: I loved being you.

672
00:43:16,681 --> 00:43:18,161
Every second of it.

673
00:43:19,201 --> 00:43:21,401
Oh, the way you burn, like a sun.

674
00:43:22,441 --> 00:43:25,361
Like a whole screaming world on fire.

675
00:43:27,041 --> 00:43:28,561
I remember that feeling,

676
00:43:29,761 --> 00:43:31,121
and I always will.

677
00:43:36,001 --> 00:43:37,761
(SOFTLY) And I will always miss it.

678
00:43:44,201 --> 00:43:45,561
Now, that

679
00:43:46,801 --> 00:43:50,281
was really, very nicely done.

680
00:43:51,641 --> 00:43:53,401
Thank you.

681
00:44:05,081 --> 00:44:07,561
It's good to know
I haven't lost my touch.

682
00:44:09,161 --> 00:44:10,721
You deserve my best.

683
00:44:16,361 --> 00:44:18,361
(ALARM BLARING)

684
00:44:22,801 --> 00:44:24,121
Oh, they love to advertise.

685
00:44:25,281 --> 00:44:28,001
We have to keep them away from the house
until everyone's clear.

686
00:44:28,081 --> 00:44:29,801
We've got to buy them time.

687
00:44:29,881 --> 00:44:30,961
All right back there?

688
00:44:31,041 --> 00:44:32,961
Hazran, keep it moving.

689
00:44:37,241 --> 00:44:38,481
BILL: And attack on both sides.

690
00:44:38,561 --> 00:44:40,321
-I'll take the back, yeah?
-Yeah.

691
00:44:41,281 --> 00:44:42,921
This is it, I'm afraid.

692
00:44:44,521 --> 00:44:46,481
So if there's anything
we ought to be saying...

693
00:44:48,481 --> 00:44:49,521
I._..

694
00:44:51,161 --> 00:44:52,441
Can't think of anything.

695
00:44:52,921 --> 00:44:54,041
Can you?

696
00:44:57,881 --> 00:44:58,921
No.

697
00:45:00,561 --> 00:45:01,601
Hey, erm...

698
00:45:02,841 --> 00:45:06,081
Oh, you know how I'm usually
all about women and then,

699
00:45:06,881 --> 00:45:08,641
kinda, people my own age.

700
00:45:10,001 --> 00:45:11,081
Yeah.

701
00:45:12,841 --> 00:45:14,121
Glad you knew that.

702
00:45:26,441 --> 00:45:27,721
Without hope...

703
00:45:29,081 --> 00:45:30,441
Without witness...

704
00:45:33,001 --> 00:45:34,761
Without reward.

705
00:45:39,801 --> 00:45:42,801
-How long do I have?
-Oh, I was precise.

706
00:45:42,881 --> 00:45:45,601
You'll be able to make it back
to your TARDIS, maybe even get a cuppa.

707
00:45:46,121 --> 00:45:47,761
Although you might leak a little.

708
00:45:48,641 --> 00:45:50,441
And then regenerate...

709
00:45:51,681 --> 00:45:52,801
into you.

710
00:45:53,201 --> 00:45:55,601
(CLICKS TONGUE)
Welcome to the sisterhood.

711
00:45:55,681 --> 00:45:56,761
THE MASTER: Missy.

712
00:45:57,761 --> 00:45:59,081
Seriously.

713
00:46:00,001 --> 00:46:02,121
-Why?
-MISSY: Oh.

714
00:46:03,161 --> 00:46:04,481
Because he's right.

715
00:46:04,961 --> 00:46:06,681
Because it's time to stand with him.

716
00:46:07,601 --> 00:46:10,641
It's where we've always been going
and it's happening now, today.

717
00:46:11,961 --> 00:46:14,161
It's time to stand with the Doctor.

718
00:46:15,721 --> 00:46:16,921
No.

719
00:46:17,721 --> 00:46:18,761
Never!

720
00:46:21,041 --> 00:46:22,721
Missy!

721
00:46:22,801 --> 00:46:24,841
I will never stand with the Doctor.

722
00:46:25,481 --> 00:46:27,881
-Yes, my dear, you will.
-(DEVICE CLICKS)

723
00:46:27,961 --> 00:46:29,561
(GASPS)

724
00:46:34,201 --> 00:46:35,521
(GROANS)

725
00:46:36,641 --> 00:46:38,761
THE MASTER: Don't bother trying
to regenerate.

726
00:46:39,321 --> 00:46:40,721
You got the full blast.

727
00:46:41,241 --> 00:46:43,241
(LAUGHING)

728
00:46:47,601 --> 00:46:49,601
(BOTH CONTINUE LAUGHING)

729
00:46:51,601 --> 00:46:57,041
You see, Missy,
this is where we've always been going.

730
00:46:57,121 --> 00:47:00,241
This is our perfect ending.

731
00:47:01,241 --> 00:47:04,321
We shoot ourselves in the back.

732
00:47:11,841 --> 00:47:13,921
-(THE MASTER GRUNTS)
-(LIFT BELL DINGS)

733
00:47:19,881 --> 00:47:21,881
(LAUGHING)

734
00:47:42,481 --> 00:47:45,361
Okay, to the lifts. Floor 502.

735
00:47:45,441 --> 00:47:48,481
Squeeze as many in as you can,
we only get one trip.

736
00:47:48,561 --> 00:47:51,841
-They'll take years to get back here.
-(EXPLOSION)

737
00:47:56,921 --> 00:47:58,081
(SOFTLY) Come along.

738
00:48:07,641 --> 00:48:10,121
Telos! Sealed you into your life-tombs!

739
00:48:12,641 --> 00:48:13,801
Voga.

740
00:48:13,881 --> 00:48:15,321
(EXPLOSION)

741
00:48:20,321 --> 00:48:21,641
Canary Wharf.

742
00:48:22,961 --> 00:48:24,321
(GRUNTS)

743
00:48:27,041 --> 00:48:28,481
Planet 14.

744
00:48:29,521 --> 00:48:30,801
Every single time.

745
00:48:33,201 --> 00:48:35,881
You lose, even on the moon.

746
00:48:41,081 --> 00:48:42,281
(SCREAMS)

747
00:48:46,081 --> 00:48:47,321
Hello.

748
00:48:48,721 --> 00:48:50,081
I'm the Doctor.

749
00:48:50,441 --> 00:48:53,321
CYBERMAN: Doctors are not required.

750
00:48:55,241 --> 00:48:56,241
(GRUNTS)

751
00:48:57,121 --> 00:48:59,641
(GROANS AND BREATHES HEAVILY)

752
00:49:00,961 --> 00:49:02,641
(RAGGEDLY) No, no.

753
00:49:04,121 --> 00:49:05,761
I'm not a doctor.

754
00:49:07,561 --> 00:49:09,401
I am the Doctor.

755
00:49:11,721 --> 00:49:14,201
The original, you might say.

756
00:49:15,921 --> 00:49:18,121
(GASPING)

757
00:49:18,961 --> 00:49:20,201
(GROANS)

758
00:49:40,401 --> 00:49:41,481
(SOFTLY) Doctor.

759
00:49:43,241 --> 00:49:44,521
Doctor.

760
00:49:45,681 --> 00:49:46,961
Let it go.

761
00:49:49,521 --> 00:49:50,921
Time enough.

762
00:49:53,481 --> 00:49:54,521
(INHALES SHARPLY)

763
00:50:11,681 --> 00:50:12,761
Pity...

764
00:50:14,481 --> 00:50:15,481
No stars.

765
00:50:20,001 --> 00:50:22,001
I hoped there'd be stars.

766
00:50:54,361 --> 00:50:55,801
ALIT: They still might come,

767
00:50:56,201 --> 00:50:57,321
your friends.

768
00:50:59,401 --> 00:51:02,441
No. No, I don't think so.

769
00:51:03,321 --> 00:51:04,681
What about the Cybermen?

770
00:51:04,761 --> 00:51:06,841
Well, the Doctor's destroyed
most of them,

771
00:51:06,921 --> 00:51:10,801
so it'll take them a while
to regroup before they find us again.

772
00:51:11,561 --> 00:51:12,921
And then what?

773
00:51:13,201 --> 00:51:14,921
Well, I'm sure I'll think of something.

774
00:51:15,001 --> 00:51:18,041
Nardole! Alit!
Hazran says the food's ready.

775
00:51:20,601 --> 00:51:23,281
All right, come on.
Let's go and find the others.

776
00:51:25,241 --> 00:51:27,601
-You know Hazran?
-Yes.

777
00:51:27,681 --> 00:51:29,481
-I think she likes you.
-(GIGGLES)

778
00:51:29,561 --> 00:51:31,761
Well, she's only human.

779
00:51:41,041 --> 00:51:43,121
(METAL CLANKING)

780
00:52:13,601 --> 00:52:15,641
(SOBBING)

781
00:52:49,601 --> 00:52:50,801
(GASPS)

782
00:53:00,841 --> 00:53:02,041
Promise you won't go?

783
00:53:02,481 --> 00:53:03,521
Promise.

784
00:53:10,041 --> 00:53:11,561
(GASPING)

785
00:53:19,241 --> 00:53:20,321
Am I dead?

786
00:53:32,001 --> 00:53:33,441
Does that feel dead to you?

787
00:53:36,081 --> 00:53:37,401
(CHUCKLES)

788
00:53:39,001 --> 00:53:42,161
You're like me now.
It's just a different kind of living.

789
00:53:43,441 --> 00:53:44,881
How did you find me?

790
00:53:47,441 --> 00:53:49,081
Left you my tears, remember?

791
00:53:56,001 --> 00:53:57,521
I don't think they're mine.

792
00:53:57,601 --> 00:53:59,561
HEATHER: I know when you're crying them.

793
00:54:01,081 --> 00:54:02,201
Time to go.

794
00:54:03,081 --> 00:54:04,601
But...

795
00:54:04,681 --> 00:54:06,841
The Doctor. We can't just leave him.

796
00:54:06,921 --> 00:54:08,281
Of course we can't.

797
00:54:09,281 --> 00:54:10,641
And we're not going to.

798
00:54:23,761 --> 00:54:26,361
BILL: 7 suppose this is the only place
he'd rest in peace.

799
00:54:33,521 --> 00:54:35,441
If there's any place he'd do that.

800
00:54:45,961 --> 00:54:47,641
How can you fly the TARDIS?

801
00:54:47,721 --> 00:54:50,481
I'm the pilot. I can fly anything.

802
00:54:51,001 --> 00:54:52,121
Even you.

803
00:54:52,481 --> 00:54:53,841
(CHUCKLES)

804
00:54:55,961 --> 00:54:57,721
So I'm like you now?

805
00:54:57,801 --> 00:55:01,361
-I'm not human any more.
-I can make you human again.

806
00:55:01,441 --> 00:55:04,921
It's all just atoms. You can
rearrange them any way you like.

807
00:55:05,441 --> 00:55:08,441
I can put you back home,
can make chips

808
00:55:08,721 --> 00:55:10,361
and live your life. Or...

809
00:55:11,441 --> 00:55:12,881
You can come with me.

810
00:55:14,241 --> 00:55:15,241
Ah...

811
00:55:18,881 --> 00:55:22,641
It's up to you, Bill,
but before you make up your mind,

812
00:55:26,521 --> 00:55:28,121
let me show you around.

813
00:55:33,321 --> 00:55:34,441
Back in time for tea?

814
00:55:35,921 --> 00:55:37,001
If you want.

815
00:55:43,881 --> 00:55:45,041
BILL: You know what, old man?

816
00:55:46,561 --> 00:55:48,601
I'm never gonna believe
you're really dead,

817
00:55:49,561 --> 00:55:52,841
'cause one day, everyone's just
gonna need you too much.

818
00:55:54,561 --> 00:55:55,761
Until then...

819
00:56:04,361 --> 00:56:05,761
It's a big universe.

820
00:56:06,401 --> 00:56:08,521
But I hope I see you again.

821
00:56:18,201 --> 00:56:20,641
Where there's tears, there's hope.

822
00:56:27,281 --> 00:56:28,321
Just one thing...

823
00:56:30,121 --> 00:56:33,241
I've been through a lot
since the last time we met...

824
00:56:36,481 --> 00:56:37,801
So I'll show you around.

825
00:57:05,921 --> 00:57:06,921
-Doctor!
-Doctor!

826
00:57:07,001 --> 00:57:08,081
Doctor!

827
00:57:10,321 --> 00:57:11,601
-Doctor?
-Doctor.

828
00:57:11,681 --> 00:57:13,121
-Doctor!
-Doctor!

829
00:57:13,201 --> 00:57:14,201
-Doctor.
-Doctor.

830
00:57:14,281 --> 00:57:15,361
-Doctor.
-Doctor.

831
00:57:15,441 --> 00:57:16,641
-Doctor?
-Doctor.

832
00:57:20,081 --> 00:57:21,121
Doctor.

833
00:57:21,201 --> 00:57:22,801
(GASPS)

834
00:57:22,881 --> 00:57:25,081
Sontarans! Perverting
the course of human history.

835
00:57:25,161 --> 00:57:26,401
(GASPING)

836
00:57:28,321 --> 00:57:29,641
I don't want to go.

837
00:57:35,841 --> 00:57:36,961
When the Doctor...

838
00:57:40,281 --> 00:57:43,761
When the Doctor was me!

839
00:57:46,361 --> 00:57:47,801
When the Doctor was me...

840
00:57:49,801 --> 00:57:51,881
(ALARM BLARING)

841
00:57:56,041 --> 00:57:57,681
It's starting.

842
00:57:58,601 --> 00:58:00,201
I'm regenerating.

843
00:58:01,121 --> 00:58:02,761
No! No!

844
00:58:03,321 --> 00:58:04,881
No! No!

845
00:58:05,241 --> 00:58:06,801
No! No!

846
00:58:10,321 --> 00:58:12,361
(TARDIS POWERS DOWN)

847
00:58:19,601 --> 00:58:20,921
Where have you taken me?

848
00:58:23,161 --> 00:58:26,801
If you're trying to make a point,
I'm not listening.

849
00:58:26,881 --> 00:58:28,521
I don't want to change again.

850
00:58:30,041 --> 00:58:31,361
Never again!

851
00:58:32,081 --> 00:58:34,241
(TARDIS BEEPING)

852
00:58:34,321 --> 00:58:36,841
I can't keep on being somebody else.

853
00:58:41,321 --> 00:58:43,001
Whatever it is...

854
00:58:44,601 --> 00:58:46,001
I'm staying.

855
00:58:53,241 --> 00:58:55,321
(DISTANT CLANGING)

856
00:58:59,841 --> 00:59:04,721
No!

857
00:59:05,641 --> 00:59:06,921
(GRUNTS)

858
00:59:08,761 --> 00:59:12,601
I will not change!

859
00:59:21,161 --> 00:59:22,841
OLD MAN: I will not change.

860
00:59:22,921 --> 00:59:26,361
I will not. No, no, no, no.
The whole thing's ridiculous.

861
00:59:27,121 --> 00:59:28,241
Hello.

862
00:59:29,001 --> 00:59:30,401
Someone there?

863
00:59:32,041 --> 00:59:33,241
OLD MAN: Who is that?

864
00:59:33,921 --> 00:59:35,201
I'm the Doctor.

865
00:59:36,641 --> 00:59:40,321
The Doctor?
No, I don't think so.

866
00:59:40,761 --> 00:59:43,081
No, dear me, no.

867
00:59:43,161 --> 00:59:46,321
You may be a doctor,

868
00:59:46,401 --> 00:59:49,241
but I am the Doctor.

869
00:59:50,881 --> 00:59:54,161
The original, you might say.

870
01:00:01,841 --> 01:00:03,881
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

